# 🚀 My Portfolio — Setup Guide

A clean, minimal dark-mode developer portfolio inspired by min-hyuk.com.
Built with pure HTML, CSS, and vanilla JavaScript. No frameworks needed.

---

## 📁 Files

```
my-portfolio/
├── index.html     ← Main page (all sections)
├── style.css      ← All styles + dark/light theme
├── script.js      ← Theme toggle, animations, copy email
└── README.md      ← This guide
```

---

## ✏️ STEP 1 — Fill In Your Info

Open `index.html` and replace all the placeholder text with yours.
Search for these exact strings and swap them out:

| Placeholder           | Replace with                      |
|-----------------------|-----------------------------------|
| `YOUR NAME`           | Your actual name                  |
| `your.email@gmail.com`| Your real email                   |
| `DD.MM.YYYY`          | Your date of birth (optional)     |
| `+91 XXXXX XXXXX`     | Your phone (optional)             |
| `Pune, India`         | Your city                         |
| `@ Your Company`      | Where you work / study now        |
| `your.email@gmail.com`| (in footer and mailto links too)  |
| GitHub / LinkedIn URLs| Your real profile URLs            |

---

## 🖼️ STEP 2 — Add Project Images

In the Projects section, each card has a `.project-img-placeholder` div.
To add a real screenshot or GIF:

1. Create a folder: `images/`
2. Put your images in it: `images/project1.png`, etc.
3. In `index.html`, replace:
   ```html
   <div class="project-img-placeholder">
     <span>PROJECT 01</span>
   </div>
   ```
   with:
   ```html
   <img src="images/project1.png" alt="Project Name" />
   ```

---

## 🔗 STEP 3 — Add Your Project Links

In each project card, update the `href` attributes:
```html
<a href="https://yourproject.vercel.app" ...>View Live ↗</a>
<a href="https://github.com/you/repo" ...>GitHub ↗</a>
```

---

## 🌐 STEP 4 — Deploy to Vercel (Free, Easiest)

### Option A — Drag & Drop (No Git needed)
1. Go to https://vercel.com and sign up (free)
2. Click "Add New Project" → "Deploy without Git"
3. Drag your entire `my-portfolio/` folder into Vercel
4. Click Deploy → your site is live in 60 seconds!
5. You'll get a free URL like `yourname.vercel.app`

### Option B — Via GitHub (Recommended for future updates)
1. Push your files to a GitHub repo
2. On Vercel → "Add New Project" → Import from GitHub
3. Select your repo → Deploy
4. Every time you push to GitHub, Vercel auto-deploys

---

## 🔗 STEP 5 — Connect Your Custom Domain

### If you bought from GoDaddy / Namecheap / Google Domains:

**On Vercel:**
1. Go to your project → Settings → Domains
2. Click "Add Domain"
3. Type your domain: `yourname.com`
4. Vercel will show you DNS records to add (usually 2 records)

**On your domain registrar (e.g. GoDaddy):**
1. Go to DNS Settings for your domain
2. Add an **A Record**:
   - Name: `@`
   - Value: `76.76.21.21` (Vercel's IP)
3. Add a **CNAME Record**:
   - Name: `www`
   - Value: `cname.vercel-dns.com`
4. Save and wait 5–30 minutes for it to propagate

**That's it!** Vercel handles HTTPS/SSL automatically for free.

---

## 🌍 STEP 6 — Deploy to GitHub Pages (Alternative, also free)

1. Push your folder to a GitHub repo named `yourusername.github.io`
2. Go to repo Settings → Pages
3. Source: "Deploy from branch" → `main` → `/root`
4. Your site is live at `https://yourusername.github.io`

**For custom domain on GitHub Pages:**
1. In repo Settings → Pages → Custom domain → type `yourname.com`
2. On your registrar, add:
   - A Records pointing to GitHub's IPs:
     ```
     185.199.108.153
     185.199.109.153
     185.199.110.153
     185.199.111.153
     ```
   - CNAME: `www` → `yourusername.github.io`

---

## 🎨 STEP 7 — Customise the Look (Optional)

Open `style.css` and find the `:root` block at the top.
You can change colours easily:

```css
:root {
  --accent: #d4c89a;   /* ← Change this to your accent colour */
  --bg: #0d0d0d;       /* ← Background */
  --text: #e8e6e0;     /* ← Main text */
}
```

Try accent colour ideas:
- Blue: `#7ab4d4`
- Green: `#7ab87a`
- Pink: `#d47ab4`
- Orange: `#d4a07a`

